Given a positive integer n, find the sum of the first n natural numbers.

Examples : 

Input: n = 3
Output: 6
Explanation: 1 + 2 + 3 = 6

Input: n = 5
Output: 15 
Explanation:  1 + 2 + 3 + 4 + 5 = 15

Naive Approach: Using Loop
Initialize sum as 0
Run a loop from i equals to 1 to n. Inside the loop add i to sum.

Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(1)

Solution:
public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
     Scanner scn=new Scanner(System.in);
     int n=scn.nextInt();
     System.out.println(NaturalNumberSum(n));
    }
   public static int NaturalNumberSum(int n)  {
         int sum=0;
         for(int i=1;i<=n;i++){
          sum+=i;
         }
         return sum;
    }
}

Using Recursion:In this approach, we use recursion to find the sum of the first n natural numbers. 
The function calls itself with (n-1) until it reaches the base case of n = 1. 
Each call adds the current value of n to the sum of smaller values, effectively building the result in a top-down manner.

Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(n)

Solution:
public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
     Scanner scn=new Scanner(System.in);
     int n=scn.nextInt();
     System.out.println(NaturalNumberSum(n));
    }
   public static int NaturalNumberSum(int n)  {
        if(n==1){
          return 1;
        }
        return n+ NaturalNumberSum(n-1);
    }
}

Using Formula Approach:
Sum of first n natural numbers = (n * (n+1)) / 2

Time Complexity: O(1)
Space Complexity: O(1)

Solution:
public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
     Scanner scn=new Scanner(System.in);
     int n=scn.nextInt();
     System.out.println(NaturalNumberSum(n));
    }
   public static int NaturalNumberSum(int n)  {
      return (n *(n+1))/2;
    }
}















